TOPIC 33:
CHLORINE AND ITS COMPOUND
DURATION: 15 Periods
By the end of this topic the learner should be able to explain the chemistry of chlorine and its compounds.
GENERAL OBJECTIVE:
SUB-TOPIC
SPECIFIC OBJECTIVE
CONTENT
Chlorine
(6 periods)
Learners should be able to:
Describe and explain the
laboratory preparation and
manufacture of chlorine.
Outline the properties of chlorine.
Outline the uses of chlorine.
Preparation of chlorine: Conc. HCI
+ Potassium mangnate (VII).
Electrolysis of chloride solutions.
Properties of chlorine gas.
- Reaction of chlorine with
metals (Mg, Fe, Na, Zn).
- Reaction of chlorine with non
metal (P, S).
Reaction of chlorine with:
Water and dilute alkali.
Bromides and iodides
Bleaching action of chlorine
- Reaction with hydrocarbons
(turpentine)
Uses of chlorine
TEACHING AND LEARNING
STRATEGIES
Carry out an experiment to
prepare chlorine.
Discuss the industrial
manufacture of chlorine.
Carry out experiments to
demonstrate the properties of
chlorine.
Brain storm on the uses of
Chlorine.
